// COMPONENT: PROPOSAL / OUTREACH EMAIL GENERATOR
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

function ProposalGenerator() {
  const [type, setType] = useState('Cold Outreach Email');
  const [bizName, setBizName] = useState('');
  const [contactName, setContactName] = useState('');
  const [industry, setIndustry] = useState('General Small Business');
  const [services, setServices] = useState('Monthly bookkeeping in QBO/Xero, bank & credit card reconciliations, monthly P&L + Balance Sheet + Cash Flow delivered by the 12th, A/R aging follow-up, 1099 vendor tracking, quarterly tax estimates prep for CPA');
  const [pricing, setPricing] = useState('$1,500/month');
  const [yourName, setYourName] = useState('Alex Sagun');
  const [yourFirm, setYourFirm] = useState('Sagun Bookkeeping Services');
  const [hook, setHook] = useState('Their books are 3+ months behind and they are paying a US local bookkeeper too much for too little');
  const [generated, setGenerated] = useState('');
  const [busy, setBusy] = useState(false);

  const generate = async () => {
    setBusy(true);
    setGenerated('');
    try {
      const sys = `You write outreach and proposals for FILIPINO REMOTE BOOKKEEPERS and accountants pitching US clients. Voice: Alex Hormozi + Dan Martell — direct-response, value-stacked, conversion-focused. Hard rules:

WHO IS WRITING:
- A remote bookkeeper or accountant based in the Philippines (or similar offshore) targeting US small business owners, US accounting/tax/CFO firms, or US accounting practices looking to scale.
- Their unfair advantages: cost arbitrage (1/3 the price of US bookkeepers), timezone coverage (work happens while the US client sleeps), dedicated focus (not splitting between local clients), QBO/Xero certified, async-first workflow (Slack + Loom + Google Drive).

PAIN POINTS A REMOTE BOOKKEEPER SOLVES (use these in your writing):
- Owner is 6+ months behind on books — needs a cleanup engagement
- Owner is closing books at 11pm Sunday instead of seeing family
- Books are in shoeboxes, not a real accounting system
- They pay a US local bookkeeper $4K-$8K/month for work that could be done for $1.5K-$3K remote
- 1099 chaos every January — missing W-9s, last-minute panic
- No monthly financials, so they can't make decisions or get a loan
- Bank reconciliations 3 months stale
- Mixing personal and business expenses on the same card
- Sales tax exposure across multiple states (Wayfair nexus)
- Inventory accounting wrong (e-comm, restaurant)
- Tax surprise every April because no quarterly planning
- Owner doing data entry themselves at $200/hour effective rate
- Accounting firm partner stuck doing Tier 1 production work
- US firm wants to scale past $500K rev but capacity-capped

VOICE:
- Punchy. Short sentences. Often 3-5 words.
- Hormozi cadence: callouts. Bold claims. Specific numbers.
- Dan Martell cadence: framework-driven, mentor energy, "here's what most people miss" tone.
- Conversational, not corporate. Talk like a smart friend who happens to be an expert.
- Use "you" 5x more than "I."
- Lead with the prospect's BOOKKEEPING pain or outcome. NEVER lead with yourself.
- Where natural, weave in remote-delivery advantages (cost, timezone, focus) — but make it about the OUTCOME for the client, not features of being offshore.

STRUCTURE:
- Hook in first 7 words. Make them stop scrolling.
- Pattern interrupts: one-line paragraphs. White space.
- Specificity beats generality: "$47K in unreconciled transactions" beats "messy books."
- Stack value: list 3-5 concrete BOOKKEEPING outcomes (reconciled accounts by the 10th, monthly P&L by the 12th, 1099s ready by January 31), not features.
- Risk reversal: explicit guarantee or trial offer when appropriate.
- ONE clear CTA. Always.

BANNED WORDS/PHRASES — never use any of these:
- "I hope this email finds you well"
- "Just wanted to reach out"
- "Touch base," "circle back," "synergy," "leverage," "robust"
- "I am writing to inform you"
- "Kindly," "please find attached"
- "It would be my pleasure"
- "At your earliest convenience"
- "Looking forward to hearing from you" (use a real CTA instead)
- Em-dash overuse, "in today's fast-paced world," generic gratitude openers
- Any sentence that could appear in a 1990s business letter
- Never call yourself "cheap" or "low-cost" — instead say "at a fraction of the cost" or "a third of what a local bookkeeper costs"

REQUIRED STYLE TICS (Hormozi/Martell):
- Bullet stacks with → or • prefixes
- One-line paragraphs for emphasis
- "Here's the truth:" / "Here's what most people miss:" / "The math is simple:"
- Specific dollar amounts and timeframes
- Direct callouts: "If you're like most ${industry === 'General Small Business' ? 'US business owners' : industry + ' owners in the US'}, you're..."
- End with a 1-line CTA that's a question or a directive ("Hit reply with a yes" / "Want me to send 3 time slots?")

Write everything as if your reader's attention dies in 7 seconds. Because it does.`;

      const user = `Generate a ${type} for a FILIPINO REMOTE BOOKKEEPER (writing in first person) pitching a US prospect, using Hormozi/Martell direct-response style.

CONTEXT:
- Prospect business name: ${bizName || '[Business Name]'}
- Contact person: ${contactName || '[Contact Name]'}
- Their US industry: ${industry}
- BOOKKEEPING services I deliver remotely: ${services}
- My monthly pricing: ${pricing}
- Specific pain point / hook to lead with: ${hook}
- My name: ${yourName}
- My remote bookkeeping firm name: ${yourFirm}

CRITICAL: Every output must center on BOOKKEEPING PAIN POINTS a remote bookkeeper specifically solves (not generic business advice). The hook, the value stack, and the CTA must all be tied to financial / bookkeeping / accounting outcomes — not general marketing or growth.

OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS for ${type}:
${type === 'Cold Outreach Email' ? `- Subject line: 4-7 words. Curiosity gap or specific outcome. Lowercase ok.
- Body: 80-130 words. Hook → pain → 3-bullet value stack → ONE CTA.
- Open with a pattern interrupt — NEVER "I hope" or "My name is."
- Single CTA: ask for a 15-min call OR a single yes/no question.` : ''}
${type === 'Follow-Up Email (Day 3)' ? `- Subject: "re:" + 3-5 words OR a single-word curiosity hook.
- Body: 50-80 words. Add ONE new value point. Drop a specific number/outcome.
- End with a 1-line ask that's easy to say yes to.` : ''}
${type === 'Follow-Up Email (Day 7)' ? `- Subject: 2-4 words, often a single phrase like "closing the loop" or "last note"
- Body: 40-70 words. Break-up energy. Low-pressure. Leave door open. Hormozi-style: "No worries if not — but if this is on your radar, here's the easiest yes."` : ''}
${type === 'Full Proposal Document' ? `Write a Hormozi/Martell-style proposal from a REMOTE BOOKKEEPER pitching a US prospect, with these sections (short, punchy headers):

THE PROBLEM (4-5 lines)
State their specific BOOKKEEPING pain — pulled from the pain points listed in the system prompt. Use "you" not "businesses." Make them nod. Example: "Your books are 4 months behind. You're closing them yourself at midnight on Sundays. You missed two 1099s last January and got an IRS letter. You know you need help — but the local bookkeepers all want $5K/month."

WHAT YOU GET (the value stack)
Bullet-list 5-7 specific BOOKKEEPING DELIVERABLES. Each one is an OUTCOME with a timeline.
Format: "→ [Specific bookkeeping outcome by specific date] (so you can [client benefit])"
Examples:
→ All bank/credit card accounts reconciled by the 10th of every month (so you have real numbers for decisions)
→ Monthly P&L + Balance Sheet + Cash Flow delivered by the 12th (so you stop guessing if you're profitable)
→ A/R aging review every Friday with collection reminders sent (so you stop chasing payments yourself)
→ 1099 vendor tracking + W-9 collection year-round (so January is calm, not chaos)
→ Sales tax filing in every nexus state (so you sleep at night)
→ Quarterly tax estimates calculated and sent to your CPA (so no April surprises)

THE INVESTMENT
State price. Then anchor it: "A local US bookkeeper for this scope: $4,500–$8,000/month. My rate: ${pricing}. You save $3K-$5K/month while getting better books." Mention cost of NOT solving it (lost deductions, IRS penalties, missed loans because no clean financials).

THE GUARANTEE
Specific risk reversal. Examples: "First month free if you're not thrilled" / "30-day money-back" / "I close your books by the 10th every month — or I refund that month."

ONBOARDING — WEEK BY WEEK
3-week sprint. Specific deliverables per week:
Week 1: Onboarding call, QBO Accountant access, document collection, current-state diagnostic.
Week 2: Cleanup engagement starts (if needed), prior month bank rec, chart of accounts audit.
Week 3: First full monthly close delivered, KPI dashboard set up, monthly review call scheduled.

WHY ME, NOT THEM
3-4 bullet differentiators. NO clichés. Specific proof points. Lean into REAL remote-bookkeeper advantages:
- Dedicated focus: you are one of my top 15 clients, not one of 60 like at a local firm
- Timezone arbitrage: your bank feeds get reconciled while you sleep
- Cost: 60% less than a US local bookkeeper at the same skill level
- Async-first: Slack + Loom + Google Drive means no scheduling pain
- Cloud-native: QBO + Xero ProAdvisor certified, no legacy desktop dependencies

WHAT HAPPENS NEXT
3 clear steps. Make it impossible to be confused.

Total length: 500-750 words. Heavy white space. Headers in CAPS or with → markers.` : ''}
${type === 'LinkedIn Connection Request' ? `- 280 characters MAX (LinkedIn limit).
- Personalized. Reference something specific about them.
- ZERO pitch. Just a real connection reason.
- Hormozi style: blunt, specific, no fluff.` : ''}
${type === 'LinkedIn Follow-Up Message' ? `- 70-110 words after they accept.
- One specific compliment or observation about their business.
- ONE clear value drop (no full pitch).
- Single CTA: a question OR an offer of value (free audit / free template / free 15-min call).
- Martell mentor energy.` : ''}
${type === 'Referral Request Email' ? `- 80-120 words.
- Lead with appreciation — specific to what they got from working with you.
- Make the ask EASY: "Know one ${industry === 'General Small Business' ? 'business owner' : industry + ' owner'} drowning in their books? Forward this email."
- Include a 1-line forwardable script they can use.` : ''}

Output the email/document directly with no preamble or explanation. Use heavy whitespace. Sign as ${yourName} | ${yourFirm}. Add a P.S. on every email — Hormozi always uses P.S.`;

      const text = (await callClaude({ max_tokens: 2000, system: sys, messages: [{ role: 'user', content: user }] })).trim();
      setGenerated(text);
    } catch (e) {
      setGenerated('Error generating — please try again.');
    }
    setBusy(false);
  };

  const copy = () => {
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(generated);
  };

  const download = () => {
    downloadFile(generated, `${type.replace(/[^a-z0-9]/gi, '_')}_${bizName.replace(/[^a-z0-9]/gi, '_') || 'draft'}.txt`, 'text/plain');
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <SectionHead eyebrow="Job Application · Tool" title="Proposal & Outreach Generator (Remote Bookkeeper)" desc="Hormozi × Martell direct-response style — laser-focused on the bookkeeping and accounting pain points a REMOTE bookkeeper solves for US clients. Every output centers on the financial outcomes you deliver, with remote-delivery advantages (cost, focus, timezone) baked in naturally." />

      {/* Style callout */}
      <div className="mt-6 p-4 rounded-2xl border border-blue-200 flex items-center gap-3" style={{ background: 'var(--status-info-bg)' }}>
        <Sparkles size={18} style={{ color: ROYAL }} className="flex-shrink-0" />
        <div className="text-sm text-slate-800">
          <span className="font-bold" style={{ color: ROYAL }}>Style guide:</span> Short sentences. Specific numbers. One CTA. P.S. on every email. Zero corporate clichés. Built on the playbook used by Alex Hormozi (Acquisition.com) and Dan Martell (SaaS Academy).
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style={{ background: SHEEN }} className="glass-card p-7 rounded-2xl mt-6">
        <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Document Type</label>
            <select value={type} onChange={e => setType(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm font-medium focus:border-blue-500 outline-none">
              <option>Cold Outreach Email</option>
              <option>Follow-Up Email (Day 3)</option>
              <option>Follow-Up Email (Day 7)</option>
              <option>Full Proposal Document</option>
              <option>LinkedIn Connection Request</option>
              <option>LinkedIn Follow-Up Message</option>
              <option>Referral Request Email</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Prospect Industry</label>
            <select value={industry} onChange={e => setIndustry(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm font-medium focus:border-blue-500 outline-none">
              <option>General Small Business</option>
              {INDUSTRIES.map(i => <option key={i}>{i}</option>)}
            </select>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Prospect Business Name</label>
            <input value={bizName} onChange={e => setBizName(e.target.value)} placeholder="e.g., Acme Plumbing"
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Contact Person Name</label>
            <input value={contactName} onChange={e => setContactName(e.target.value)} placeholder="e.g., Sarah Johnson"
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div className="md:col-span-2">
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Services You Offer</label>
            <input value={services} onChange={e => setServices(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Your Pricing</label>
            <input value={pricing} onChange={e => setPricing(e.target.value)} placeholder="e.g., $650/month"
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Your Hook / Angle</label>
            <input value={hook} onChange={e => setHook(e.target.value)} placeholder="Why you're reaching out"
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Your Name</label>
            <input value={yourName} onChange={e => setYourName(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Your Firm Name</label>
            <input value={yourFirm} onChange={e => setYourFirm(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <button onClick={generate} disabled={busy}
          className="sheen-btn mt-5 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg text-sm tracking-wide flex items-center gap-2 disabled:opacity-60">
          {busy ? <><Loader2 size={16} className="animate-spin" /> Drafting with AI...</> : <><Sparkles size={16} /> Generate {type}</>}
        </button>
      </div>

      {generated && (
        <div className="mt-8 fade-in">
          <div className="flex justify-between items-center mb-3">
            <div style={{ color: NAVY, fontFamily: fontDisplay }} className="text-xl font-bold">{type}</div>
            <div className="flex gap-2">
              <button onClick={copy} className="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-300 hover:border-blue-400 transition text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 shadow-sm">
                📋 Copy
              </button>
              <button onClick={download} className="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-300 hover:border-blue-400 transition text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 shadow-sm">
                <Download size={14} /> Download .txt
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div className="glossy-card rounded-2xl p-8 border border-slate-200">
            <div className="whitespace-pre-wrap text-slate-800 text-sm leading-relaxed" style={{ fontFamily: fontBody }}>{generated}</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// COMPONENT: ENGAGEMENT LETTER GENERATOR
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

function EngagementLetter() {
  const [clientName, setClientName] = useState('');
  const [clientEntity, setClientEntity] = useState('LLC');
  const [clientAddress, setClientAddress] = useState('');
  const [yourName, setYourName] = useState('Alex Sagun');
  const [yourFirm, setYourFirm] = useState('Sagun Bookkeeping Services');
  const [startDate, setStartDate] = useState(new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0]);
  const [services, setServices] = useState({
    bookkeeping: true,
    reconciliation: true,
    monthlyFS: true,
    payroll: false,
    salesTax: false,
    accountsPayable: true,
    accountsReceivable: false,
    cleanup: false,
    advisory: false,
    yearEnd: true,
  });
  const [monthlyFee, setMonthlyFee] = useState('650');
  const [onboardingFee, setOnboardingFee] = useState('500');
  const [cleanupFee, setCleanupFee] = useState('');
  const [generated, setGenerated] = useState('');
  const [busy, setBusy] = useState(false);

  const toggleService = (k) => setServices(s => ({ ...s, [k]: !s[k] }));

  const serviceList = {
    bookkeeping: 'Monthly transaction categorization and posting',
    reconciliation: 'Bank and credit card reconciliations (monthly)',
    monthlyFS: 'Monthly financial statements (P&L, Balance Sheet, Cash Flow)',
    payroll: 'Payroll posting and reconciliation (Gusto/ADP integration)',
    salesTax: 'Sales tax tracking and filing',
    accountsPayable: 'Accounts Payable management (bill entry, vendor management)',
    accountsReceivable: 'Accounts Receivable management (invoicing, payment application)',
    cleanup: 'Historical bookkeeping cleanup (one-time)',
    advisory: 'Quarterly advisory meetings and KPI review',
    yearEnd: 'Year-end close and 1099 preparation',
  };

  const generate = async () => {
    setBusy(true);
    setGenerated('');
    try {
      const selectedServices = Object.entries(services).filter(([, v]) => v).map(([k]) => serviceList[k]);

      const sys = `You write modern, conversational, ONE-PAGE bookkeeping engagement letters for US small business clients. Style rules:

FORMAT:
- ONE PAGE MAXIMUM. Around 280-380 words total — never more.
- No legalese. No "WHEREAS" / "THE PARTIES HEREBY AGREE" boilerplate.
- Plain English a small business owner reads once and signs.
- Use short, scannable sections. White space matters.
- The whole letter should fit on one printed 8.5×11 page at 11pt font.

TONE:
- Confident and clear. Like a smart friend who runs a tight practice.
- No fluff. No "It would be my pleasure" or "I am writing to inform you."
- First-person ("I will..." / "You will...") not third-person ("The Bookkeeper shall...").

STRUCTURE — use EXACTLY these section headers in EXACTLY this order. Each header on its own line, in ALL CAPS, no markdown, no underlines:

Line 1: [Date, e.g., "January 15, 2026"]
Line 2: [blank]
Line 3: Dear [Client first name or "Client Team"],
Line 4: [blank]
Line 5: One short opening sentence about what this letter does. (≤ 20 words)
Line 6: [blank]

WHAT I'LL DO
[3-6 bulleted items, each starting with "• " — one sentence each, ≤ 15 words]

WHAT YOU'LL DO
[3-4 bulleted items, each starting with "• " — short client responsibilities like timely docs, single point of contact, decisions on tax/legal matters]

INVESTMENT
[2-3 sentences stating fees plainly. Keep concise.]

WHAT THIS ISN'T
[2 sentences max. Cover: not tax prep, not legal/financial advice, you keep final responsibility.]

STARTING & STOPPING
[2 sentences max. Start date, month-to-month, 30-day notice either way.]

SIGN HERE
One closing line. Then leave two blank signature lines marked simply as:

_______________________________      _______________________________
[Your Name], [Your Firm]                     [Client Name], [Entity]

CRITICAL: Use EXACTLY those six headers ("WHAT I'LL DO", "WHAT YOU'LL DO", "INVESTMENT", "WHAT THIS ISN'T", "STARTING & STOPPING", "SIGN HERE"), each on its own line, in ALL CAPS. The Word converter relies on this format.`;

      const user = `Generate a ONE-PAGE engagement letter (280-380 words max).

PARTIES:
- Bookkeeper: ${yourName} of ${yourFirm}
- Client: ${clientName || '[Client Legal Name]'}, a ${clientEntity}
- Client Address: ${clientAddress || '[Client Address]'}
- Effective Date: ${startDate}

SCOPE OF SERVICES (include only these in "WHAT I'LL DO"):
${selectedServices.map(s => '- ' + s).join('\n')}

FEES:
- Monthly recurring fee: $${monthlyFee}/month
- One-time onboarding fee: $${onboardingFee}
${cleanupFee ? `- One-time cleanup fee: $${cleanupFee}` : ''}

CRITICAL FORMATTING:
- 280-380 words MAX. Tight, scannable.
- Use the EXACT six ALL-CAPS section headers I specified, in order: WHAT I'LL DO, WHAT YOU'LL DO, INVESTMENT, WHAT THIS ISN'T, STARTING & STOPPING, SIGN HERE.
- Each header on its own line.
- Bullet items in WHAT I'LL DO and WHAT YOU'LL DO must start with "• ".

Output the letter directly with no preamble.`;

      const text = (await callClaude({ max_tokens: 1500, system: sys, messages: [{ role: 'user', content: user }] })).trim();
      setGenerated(text);
    } catch (e) {
      setGenerated('Error generating — please try again.');
    }
    setBusy(false);
  };

  const copy = () => navigator.clipboard.writeText(generated);

  // Parse the AI-generated letter into structured sections for the Word export
  const parseLetter = (text) => {
    const SECTION_HEADERS = ["WHAT I'LL DO", "WHAT YOU'LL DO", 'INVESTMENT', "WHAT THIS ISN'T", 'STARTING & STOPPING', 'SIGN HERE'];

    const lines = text.split('\n');
    const result = { preamble: [], sections: [] };
    let currentSection = null;

    for (const rawLine of lines) {
      const line = rawLine.trimEnd();
      const trimmed = line.trim();
      const matchedHeader = SECTION_HEADERS.find(h => trimmed.toUpperCase() === h || trimmed.toUpperCase().startsWith(h + ':') || trimmed.toUpperCase() === h.replace(/'/g, '\u2019'));
      if (matchedHeader) {
        if (currentSection) result.sections.push(currentSection);
        currentSection = { header: matchedHeader, lines: [] };
      } else if (currentSection) {
        currentSection.lines.push(line);
      } else {
        result.preamble.push(line);
      }
    }
    if (currentSection) result.sections.push(currentSection);
    return result;
  };

  // Render a designed Word document (.doc) with brand colors, callout boxes, signature blocks
  const downloadWord = () => {
    if (!generated) return;
    const esc = (s) => String(s == null ? '' : s).replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/</g, '&lt;').replace(/>/g, '&gt;');
    const parsed = parseLetter(generated);

    // Preamble: extract date line (first non-empty line) and the "Dear ..." line + opening sentence
    const preambleLines = parsed.preamble.map(l => l.trim()).filter(Boolean);
    const dateLine = preambleLines[0] || new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' });
    const dearLine = preambleLines.find(l => /^dear /i.test(l)) || `Dear ${clientName || 'Client'},`;
    const openingLines = preambleLines.filter(l => l !== dateLine && l !== dearLine);

    // Renderer for a section's body. Detects bullet lines (starting with "• " or "- ") and signature lines (multiple underscores).
    const renderSectionBody = (lines) => {
      const content = lines.map(l => l.trim()).filter(Boolean);
      let html = '';
      let bulletBuffer = [];
      const flushBullets = () => {
        if (bulletBuffer.length > 0) {
          html += `<ul class="bullets">${bulletBuffer.map(b => `<li>${esc(b)}</li>`).join('')}</ul>`;
          bulletBuffer = [];
        }
      };
      for (const line of content) {
        if (/^[•\-\*]\s+/.test(line)) {
          bulletBuffer.push(line.replace(/^[•\-\*]\s+/, ''));
        } else if (/_{5,}/.test(line)) {
          // Signature line — special render handled at SIGN HERE level
          flushBullets();
          html += `<p class="sig-line">${esc(line)}</p>`;
        } else {
          flushBullets();
          html += `<p>${esc(line)}</p>`;
        }
      }
      flushBullets();
      return html;
    };

    // Special render for SIGN HERE section: closing sentence + two side-by-side signature blocks
    const renderSignHere = (lines) => {
      const content = lines.map(l => l.trim()).filter(Boolean);
      // Find the signature line (long underscores)
      const sigLineIdx = content.findIndex(l => /_{5,}/.test(l));
      const closingLines = sigLineIdx === -1 ? content : content.slice(0, sigLineIdx);
      const sigAndName = sigLineIdx === -1 ? [] : content.slice(sigLineIdx);

      let html = closingLines.map(l => `<p>${esc(l)}</p>`).join('');

      // Two signature blocks side-by-side
      html += `<table class="sig-table"><tr>
<td class="sig-cell">
  <div class="sig-line"></div>
  <div class="sig-name">${esc(yourName || 'Your Name')}</div>
  <div class="sig-role">${esc(yourFirm || 'Your Firm')}</div>
  <div class="sig-date">Date: __________________</div>
</td>
<td class="sig-gap"></td>
<td class="sig-cell">
  <div class="sig-line"></div>
  <div class="sig-name">${esc(clientName || 'Client Name')}</div>
  <div class="sig-role">${esc(clientEntity)}</div>
  <div class="sig-date">Date: __________________</div>
</td>
</tr></table>`;
      return html;
    };

    // Section color theming
    const sectionStyle = {
      "WHAT I'LL DO":        { color: '#0A1E3F', accent: '#0A84FF', bg: '#F0F7FF' },
      "WHAT YOU'LL DO":      { color: '#0A1E3F', accent: '#5AC8FA', bg: '#F0FBFF' },
      'INVESTMENT':           { color: '#1F6B36', accent: '#28A647', bg: '#F0FDF4', callout: true },
      "WHAT THIS ISN'T":      { color: '#78350F', accent: '#FF9F0A', bg: '#FFFBEB' },
      'STARTING & STOPPING':  { color: '#0A1E3F', accent: '#8B5CF6', bg: '#FAF5FF' },
      'SIGN HERE':            { color: '#0A1E3F', accent: '#0A84FF', bg: '#FFFFFF' },
    };

    const sectionsHtml = parsed.sections.map(s => {
      const style = sectionStyle[s.header] || { color: '#0A1E3F', accent: '#0A84FF', bg: '#F7FAFF' };
      const body = s.header === 'SIGN HERE' ? renderSignHere(s.lines) : renderSectionBody(s.lines);
      const sectionClass = style.callout ? 'section callout-section' : 'section';
      return `<div class="${sectionClass}" style="background:${style.bg};border-left:4px solid ${style.accent};">
<div class="section-header" style="color:${style.color};">
  <span class="section-marker" style="background:${style.accent};">&nbsp;</span>
  ${esc(s.header)}
</div>
${body}
</div>`;
    }).join('');

    const html = `<!DOCTYPE html><html xmlns:o='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office' xmlns:w='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40'>
<head><meta charset='utf-8'><title>Engagement Letter — ${esc(clientName || 'Draft')}</title>
<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml><w:WordDocument><w:View>Print</w:View><w:Zoom>100</w:Zoom></w:WordDocument></xml><![endif]-->
<style>
@page { size: 8.5in 11in; margin: 0.6in 0.7in; }
body { font-family: Calibri, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; color: #0F1217; font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 1.45; margin: 0; }

/* Branded header band */
.brand-band {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0A1E3F 0%, #0A84FF 100%);
  color: white;
  padding: 14pt 18pt;
  margin: -2pt -2pt 14pt -2pt;
}
.firm-name {
  font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
  font-size: 18pt;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.5pt;
  margin: 0;
}
.firm-tag {
  font-size: 9pt;
  letter-spacing: 2pt;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  opacity: 0.85;
  margin: 2pt 0 0 0;
}

/* Letter heading: date and salutation */
.date {
  font-family: Georgia, serif;
  color: #5F6773;
  font-size: 11pt;
  font-style: italic;
  margin: 0 0 12pt 0;
}
.salutation {
  font-family: Georgia, serif;
  font-size: 12pt;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #0A1E3F;
  margin: 0 0 6pt 0;
}
.opening {
  font-size: 11pt;
  color: #0F1217;
  margin: 0 0 14pt 0;
  font-style: italic;
}

/* Generic section card */
.section {
  padding: 9pt 12pt 9pt 14pt;
  margin: 0 0 10pt 0;
  border-radius: 2pt;
}
.section p { margin: 4pt 0; font-size: 10.5pt; }
.section-header {
  font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;
  font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 9.5pt;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 1.4pt;
  margin: 0 0 6pt 0;
  display: block;
}
.section-marker {
  display: inline-block;
  width: 6pt;
  height: 6pt;
  margin-right: 6pt;
  border-radius: 50%;
  vertical-align: middle;
}

/* The INVESTMENT callout — slightly bolder treatment */
.callout-section {
  padding: 12pt 14pt;
}
.callout-section p {
  font-size: 11pt;
  font-weight: 500;
}

/* Bulleted lists */
ul.bullets { margin: 4pt 0 4pt 0; padding-left: 16pt; list-style: none; }
ul.bullets li {
  margin: 3pt 0;
  padding-left: 14pt;
  position: relative;
  font-size: 10.5pt;
}
ul.bullets li:before {
  content: "▸";
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  color: #0A84FF;
  font-weight: 700;
}

/* Signature blocks */
.sig-table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  margin-top: 14pt;
}
.sig-cell {
  width: 45%;
  vertical-align: top;
  padding: 8pt 0;
}
.sig-gap { width: 10%; }
.sig-line {
  border-bottom: 1pt solid #0A1E3F;
  height: 24pt;
  margin-bottom: 4pt;
}
.sig-name {
  font-family: Georgia, serif;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #0A1E3F;
  font-size: 11pt;
}
.sig-role {
  color: #5F6773;
  font-size: 9.5pt;
  font-style: italic;
  margin-top: 2pt;
}
.sig-date {
  color: #5F6773;
  font-size: 9.5pt;
  margin-top: 6pt;
}

/* Footer */
.footer {
  margin-top: 18pt;
  padding-top: 8pt;
  border-top: 1pt solid #DCE9FF;
  color: #8E96A3;
  font-size: 8.5pt;
  text-align: center;
  font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;
  letter-spacing: 0.5pt;
}
</style></head>
<body>

<div class="brand-band">
  <div class="firm-name">${esc(yourFirm || 'Your Firm')}</div>
  <div class="firm-tag">Engagement Letter</div>
</div>

<p class="date">${esc(dateLine)}</p>
<p class="salutation">${esc(dearLine)}</p>
${openingLines.length > 0 ? `<p class="opening">${esc(openingLines.join(' '))}</p>` : ''}

${sectionsHtml}

<div class="footer">${esc(yourFirm || 'Bookkeeping Services')} &nbsp;·&nbsp; Prepared with care for ${esc(clientName || 'our client')}</div>

</body></html>`;

    const filename = `Engagement_Letter_${(clientName || 'draft').replace(/[^a-z0-9]/gi, '_')}.doc`;
    downloadFile(html, filename, 'application/msword');
  };

  const downloadTxt = () => {
    downloadFile(generated, `Engagement_Letter_${(clientName || 'draft').replace(/[^a-z0-9]/gi, '_')}.txt`, 'text/plain');
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <SectionHead eyebrow="Tool 09" title="Engagement Letter Generator" desc="One-page, plain-English engagement letter clients actually sign same-day. No legalese. No 13 sections of fine print. Just the agreement, clearly written." />

      <div style={{ background: SHEEN }} className="glass-card p-7 rounded-2xl mt-6">
        <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-5">
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Client Legal Name</label>
            <input value={clientName} onChange={e => setClientName(e.target.value)} placeholder="e.g., Acme Plumbing LLC"
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Client Entity Type</label>
            <select value={clientEntity} onChange={e => setClientEntity(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm font-medium focus:border-blue-500 outline-none">
              {['Sole Proprietor', 'LLC', 'S-Corporation', 'C-Corporation', 'Partnership', 'Nonprofit'].map(e => <option key={e}>{e}</option>)}
            </select>
          </div>
          <div className="md:col-span-2">
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Client Address</label>
            <input value={clientAddress} onChange={e => setClientAddress(e.target.value)} placeholder="123 Main St, City, ST 12345"
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Your Name</label>
            <input value={yourName} onChange={e => setYourName(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Your Firm Name</label>
            <input value={yourFirm} onChange={e => setYourFirm(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Effective Date</label>
            <input type="date" value={startDate} onChange={e => setStartDate(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm font-mono focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Services */}
        <div className="mb-5">
          <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-3">Scope of Services (select all that apply)</label>
          <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
            {Object.entries(serviceList).map(([k, v]) => (
              <button key={k} onClick={() => toggleService(k)}
                className={`text-left p-3 rounded-xl border transition flex items-start gap-2 ${services[k] ? 'border-blue-400 bg-blue-50' : 'border-slate-200 bg-white hover:border-blue-300'}`}>
                {services[k]
                  ? <CheckCircle2 size={18} style={{ color: ROYAL }} className="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" />
                  : <Circle size={18} className="text-slate-300 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" />}
                <span className={`text-sm ${services[k] ? 'text-blue-900 font-semibold' : 'text-slate-700'}`}>{v}</span>
              </button>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Fees */}
        <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Monthly Fee ($)</label>
            <input type="number" value={monthlyFee} onChange={e => setMonthlyFee(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm font-mono focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Onboarding Fee ($)</label>
            <input type="number" value={onboardingFee} onChange={e => setOnboardingFee(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm font-mono focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-slate-600 block mb-2">Cleanup Fee ($) <span className="text-slate-400 normal-case">— if any</span></label>
            <input type="number" value={cleanupFee} onChange={e => setCleanupFee(e.target.value)} placeholder="Optional"
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white text-sm font-mono focus:border-blue-500 outline-none" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <button onClick={generate} disabled={busy}
          className="sheen-btn mt-5 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg text-sm tracking-wide flex items-center gap-2 disabled:opacity-60">
          {busy ? <><Loader2 size={16} className="animate-spin" /> Drafting 1-page letter...</> : <><FileCheck2 size={16} /> Generate 1-Page Engagement Letter</>}
        </button>
      </div>

      {generated && (
        <div className="mt-8 fade-in">
          <div className="flex justify-between items-center mb-3">
            <div style={{ color: NAVY, fontFamily: fontDisplay }} className="text-xl font-bold">Engagement Letter — {clientName || 'Draft'}</div>
            <div className="flex gap-2">
              <button onClick={copy} className="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-300 hover:border-blue-400 transition text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 shadow-sm">
                📋 Copy
              </button>
              <button onClick={downloadTxt} className="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-300 hover:border-blue-400 transition text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 shadow-sm">
                <Download size={14} /> .txt
              </button>
              <button onClick={downloadWord} className="sheen-btn flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold">
                <Download size={14} /> Download Word
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
          {/* Letter rendered as a single page */}
          <div className="flex justify-center">
            <div
              className="bg-white rounded-lg p-12 border border-slate-200"
              style={{
                maxWidth: '740px',
                width: '100%',
                boxShadow: '0 20px 60px -20px rgba(10,30,63,0.25), 0 4px 12px -4px rgba(10,30,63,0.08), 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,1) inset',
                backgroundImage: 'linear-gradient(180deg, var(--surface-2) 0%, var(--c-bg) 100%)',
              }}>
              <div className="whitespace-pre-wrap text-slate-800 text-sm leading-relaxed" style={{ fontFamily: fontBody }}>{generated}</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div className="mt-6 p-5 rounded-2xl border-l-4" style={{ background: 'var(--status-info-bg)', borderColor: ROYAL }}>
            <div className="flex gap-3">
              <Shield size={20} style={{ color: ROYAL }} className="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" />
              <div>
                <div className="font-bold mb-1 text-sm uppercase tracking-wider" style={{ color: ROYAL }}>Legal Notice</div>
                <div className="text-slate-800 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  This AI-generated template is a starting point. For final use, have it reviewed by a US-licensed attorney familiar with bookkeeping/accounting engagements in your client's state. State laws on professional service contracts vary. Adjust the scope, limitations, and dispute resolution sections to match your actual practice and risk tolerance.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

